race.comment: Handy little sprint. REY MAGNERIO (1) stays at 1000m having won the Caulfield Sprint first up, nearly a tragedy beaten when held up before charging through a late gap to win impressively. He's better over slightly further but finds a very winnable race for his level of ability and all things equal he should be too strong late. PRAIRIE FLOWER (10) is going okay and the straight should suit her turn of foot if she can land close enough. MANOLO BLING (12) is suited at 1000m first up with come competitive numbers at the distance. She goes well fresh and can land up on speed with Tim Clark booked to ride. STOKKE (14) and TREMBLES (15) are both speedy mares suited at 1000m. There wasn't much between the pair two back and both have some claims.
